# Application Framework - AI Incident Intelligence Platform
## FastAPI
FastAPI:
async support
great for microservices
automatic OpenAPI docs
simple dependency injection
perfect for internal automation tools

Typical use:
API to trigger postmortem generation
orchestrator service
pipeline control

Example Endpoint -->
POST /generate-postmortem
{
  "incident_sys_id": "abc123"
}

## Agent Orchestration Framework
LangGraph:

deterministic flows
retries
human review steps
agent state memory

multiple agents:
Extractor
Classifier
Timeline
Validator
Writer
Publisher

Example flow:
extract_data
   ↓
filter_noise
   ↓
build_timeline
   ↓
validate_quality
   ↓
generate_summary
   ↓
publish_confluence

## ServiceNow Integration
ServiceNow REST API
Pull data:
incident table
sys_audit
sys_journal_field
cmdb_ci
Python integration:
requests
httpx
pysnow (optional)

## Confluence Integration
Confluence Cloud REST API
creating postmortem pages
updating drafts
linking incidents

Example endpoint --> POST /wiki/rest/api/content
Python tools:
atlassian-python-api
or
requests

## Task Queue / Background Execution
 --> Incident analysis should run async.
 --> Celery OR simpler if GCP


## Google Cloud Tasks
Tasks handled:
extract incident
analyze timeline
generate RCA
publish page

## Data Storage

Ingestion Process:
pipeline runs
timeline events
scoring results
LLM outputs

PostgreSQL: Recommended tables

incident_pipeline_runs
incident_events
timeline_events
quality_scores
llm_outputs

## Observability Framework
pipeline observability

OpenTelemetry:
pipeline latency
agent execution time
LLM latency
failure rate

Logging

Structured logging is critical.

🪵 structlog

Logs should include

incident_id
stage
confidence_score
execution_time
Containerization
🐳 Docker

service will run as:

incident-postmortem-agent
Deployment Platform

Since you already work heavily in GCP:

## Google Cloud Run
Why Cloud Run:
autoscaling
simple deployment
cheap
no infra management

